@@eThe Saltglass Reach: Jurisdictional Gradient Analysis@@N

@@yBureau of Eastern Routes, Maritime Transition Division@@N
@@dFiled under: Legal Gradient, Shoreward Conversion, Cairn Restoration@@N

The Saltglass Reach presents the most sophisticated jurisdictional
architecture our Bureau has documented outside Midgaard itself. A
@@ylegal gradient@@N -- not a border but a continuous transformation from
inland charter law to maritime risk law across four terrain bands.
Our clerks study it the way architects study bridges.

The @@yShoreward Conversion@@N deserves attention. Specialist @@WShoreward
Assessors@@N bridged legal traditions through conversion charts.
Water-debt was discharged by pouring a measured volume onto basalt.
Cargo owners spoke formulaic oaths transferring liability from road
to sea. This is @@ejurisdiction transfer as ritual infrastructure@@N --
we recognize it because our own gate protocols perform analogous
conversions when forest-law goods enter city-law markets.

The @@yTariff Cairn Lines@@N are what our restoration advocates petition
for. Three parallel checkpoint chains -- Swift Line, Heavy Road, and
Sealed Route -- once managed traffic our Bureau estimates at four
times current eastern throughput. The cairn lines represent a
@@ysystem worth restoring@@N. Our Maritime Transition Division has
submitted proposals in three consecutive budget cycles. The
Ledgerhouse has approved none, citing @@dinsufficient jurisdiction
and excessive reconstruction cost@@N.

The @@WMirror Flats@@N blind by day, reflect moonlight by night. Our
convoy advisories restrict crossing to dawn and dusk windows,
inherited directly from the Reach's original traffic management.
The @@rGlasswind Belts@@N require specialized navigation: milky shards
mean stable ground, amber warns of thermal fault proximity,
@@dviolet signals eclipse-rite residue@@N. Our patrol manual reproduces
these color readings verbatim.

@@gReach Wardens@@N issue transit seals our gate clerks accept with
@@dcautious recognition@@N -- not full legal weight, but acknowledged
provenance. @@dGlasswalk Guides@@N maintain strict neutrality. We hold
standing contracts with three guide families, renewed each solstice.

The @@rRed Sand Outriders@@N and @@rSynod Whisper Cells@@N represent the
gradient's failure modes: predatory finance and contraband transit
exploiting jurisdictional seams.

The Reach proves that @@ylegal transitions can be engineered@@N. It
also proves they require maintenance. Every collapsed cairn is a
joint that once held two systems together. Our Bureau maintains a
registry of every cairn's last known position -- the @@dGradient
Inventory@@N. It grows longer each year, and shorter in function.
